03/09/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Prime Minister Adrian Nastase, head of the ruling Social Democratic Party (PSD), may nominate Foreign Minister Mircea Geoana to run as the partyâ€™s candidate for prime minister, according to the local press. The nomination could take place as early as Friday (3 September). Geoana is regarded as one of the most trusted PSD officials and is widely considered a strong choice for the November general elections. Nastase plans to run for president, while incumbent Ion Iliescu has agreed to take over the helm of the PSD after his term expires. (Ziua, Rompres - 03/09/04)
